{{update|date=March 2018|reason=no information since LG owned webOS}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} '''[[WebOS]]''' is a [[Linux]] [[operating system]] for [[smart device]]s, and formerly a [[mobile operating system]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.openwebosproject.org/docs/architecture |title=Open webOS :: Open webOS Architecture |publisher=Openwebosproject.org |date= |accessdate=2013-06-14}}</ref> It was initially developed by [[Palm, Inc.|Palm]], which was later acquired by [[Hewlett-Packard]], and then [[LG Electronics]]. Palm launched WebOS in January 2009. Various versions of WebOS have been featured on several devices, including [[Palm Pre|Pre]], [[Palm Pixi|Pixi]], and [[HP Veer|Veer]] phones and the [[HP TouchPad]] tablet. The latest version, 3.0.5, was released on 12 January 2012.
